Can you replace the method in `JsonParser` with this and see if it works.

```
@SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
public static Object toTypedObject(Object value, Class<?> type) {
    Assert.notNull(value, "value cannot be null");
    Assert.notNull(type, "type cannot be null");

    var javaType = ClassUtils.resolvePrimitiveIfNecessary(type);

    if (javaType.isEnum()) {
        return Enum.valueOf((Class<Enum>) javaType, value.toString());
    }

    // Delegate everything else to ObjectMapper
    return OBJECT_MAPPER.convertValue(value, javaType);
}
```

An option is to use BigDecimal and then parse it to an int or long

```
public static Object toTypedObject(Object value, Class<?> type) {
		Assert.notNull(value, "value cannot be null");
		Assert.notNull(type, "type cannot be null");

		var javaType = ClassUtils.resolvePrimitiveIfNecessary(type);

		if (javaType == String.class) {
			return value.toString();
		}
		else if (javaType == Byte.class) {
			return Byte.parseByte(value.toString());
		}
		else if (javaType == Integer.class) {
			BigDecimal decimal = new BigDecimal(value.toString());
			return decimal.intValueExact();
		}
		else if (javaType == Short.class) {
			return Short.parseShort(value.toString());
		}
		else if (javaType == Long.class) {
			BigDecimal decimal = new BigDecimal(value.toString());
			return decimal.longValueExact();
		}
		else if (javaType == Double.class) {
			return Double.parseDouble(value.toString());
		}
		else if (javaType == Float.class) {
			return Float.parseFloat(value.toString());
		}
		else if (javaType == Boolean.class) {
			return Boolean.parseBoolean(value.toString());
		}
		else if (javaType.isEnum()) {
			return Enum.valueOf((Class<Enum>) javaType, value.toString());
		}

		String json = JsonParser.toJson(value);
		return JsonParser.fromJson(json, javaType);
	}
```

